User can login in to its <account>
All clients and account info is stored in <storage>
<Client> has <ClientID> and <Client secret> and <RedirectURI> list
<Client> makes auth request that redirects user to <OpenID Provider> 
if user authenticates <OP> redirects it to <callback> link, this callback link contains <authorization code>
<Client> makes token request to switch <authtoken> to <access token>
<Client> makes request with <access token> to <Resource server>
<Resource Server> check validity of <access token>
each <access token> is binded to <account>

Ubiquitous Language: User, Client, Storage, RedirectURI, OpenID Proviver, access token, authcode, Resource Server, callback

